---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Uses" description="Hardware, software, and services I use daily.">
  <section class="py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
        <h1>Uses</h1>
        <p>
          This is my digital toolbox — the stuff that's survived real-world use. Everything here has a story,
          usually involving at least one failure before I figured it out.
        </p>
        <hr />
        <h2>Hardware</h2>
        <h3>Workstation</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Desktop PC</strong> — Intel i9-9900K, 64GB RAM, RTX 3090 (24GB VRAM), 1TB NVMe + 8TB HDD</li>
          <li><strong>Monitors</strong> — Dual 27" 4K IPS displays</li>
          <li><strong>Keyboard</strong> — Mechanical with Cherry MX Brown switches</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Homelab</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Server</strong> — Dell PowerEdge with Proxmox VE</li>
          <li><strong>Networking</strong> — UniFi Dream Machine Pro, managed switches</li>
          <li><strong>Storage</strong> — TrueNAS Scale with ZFS</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Software</h2>
        <h3>Development</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Editor</strong> — VS Code + Neovim for terminal</li>
          <li><strong>Terminal</strong> — Ghostty + tmux</li>
          <li><strong>Shell</strong> — Zsh with Oh My Zsh</li>
          <li><strong>AI</strong> — Claude Code, local LLMs via Ollama</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Security</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Password Manager</strong> — Bitwarden (self-hosted Vaultwarden)</li>
          <li><strong>VPN</strong> — WireGuard (self-hosted)</li>
          <li><strong>DNS</strong> — Pi-hole + Unbound</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
